# =============================================================================
# MCP SERVER ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# GitHub - Code repository management
# Create at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Permissions: repo, read:org, read:user
GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token_here

# Supabase MCP Server
# Get from: https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_supabase_access_token_here
SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF=your_supabase_project_reference_here

# Netlify - Static site deployment
# Get from: https://app.netlify.com/user/applications#personal-access-tokens
NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=your_netlify_auth_token_here

# Cloudinary - Image and video management
# Get from: https://cloudinary.com/console/settings/api-keys
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_cloud_name_here
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_cloudinary_api_key_here
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_cloudinary_api_secret_here

# Firecrawl - Web scraping service
# Get from: https://www.firecrawl.dev/app/api-keys
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=your_firecrawl_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual API keys
# 2. Never commit .env to git - it should be in your .gitignore
# 3. The MCP servers (memory, filesystem, fetch, puppeteer, sequential-thinking) 
#    work without API keys
# 4. URL-based servers (vercel) don't need environment variables
# 5. Remove unused services to keep your .env clean

# =============================================================================
# GETTING STARTED
# =============================================================================

# For basic MCP functionality, you only need:
# - GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN (for GitHub integration)
# - SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN and SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF (for database operations)

# For full web development workflow, also configure:
# - NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN (if using Netlify for deployment)
# - CLOUDINARY_* (if using image/video management)
# - FIRECRAWL_API_KEY (if using web scraping)